quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
  79,43,"In what [position] are you that you should mention it?{1}",footnotes:1:Meaning that Muḥammad (ﷺ) had no knowledge of it, so how could he inform them?
  79,44,"To your Lord is its finality.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., its destination and termination. And to Him belongs ultimate knowledge of it.
  79,45,"You are only a warner for those who fear it."
  80,40,"And [other] faces, that Day, will have upon them dust."
  80,41,"Blackness will cover them."
  80,42,"Those are the disbelievers, the wicked ones."
  83,28,"A spring from which those near [to Allāh] drink."
  83,29,"Indeed, those who committed crimes used to laugh at those who believed."
  83,30,"And when they passed by them, they would exchange derisive glances."
  84,25,"Except for those who believe and do righteous deeds. For them is a reward uninterrupted."
  85,22,"[Inscribed] in a Preserved Slate."
  86,16,"But I am planning a plan."
  86,17,"So allow time for the disbelievers. Leave them awhile.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., Do not be in haste for revenge, for you will see what will become of them.
  87,13,"Neither dying therein nor living."
  87,14,"He has certainly succeeded who purifies himself"
  87,15,"And mentions the name of his Lord and prays."
  88,10,"In an elevated garden,"
  88,11,"Wherein they will hear no unsuitable speech.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., any insult, falsehood, immorality, idle or vain talk, etc.
  88,12,"Within it is a flowing spring."
  89,7,"[With] Iram{1} - who had lofty pillars,{2}",footnotes:1:[Another name for the first people of ʿAad, to whom Prophet Hūd was sent.],footnotes:2:[Supporting their tents or buildings.]
  89,8,"The likes of whom had never been created in the land?"
  89,9,"And [with] Thamūd, who carved out the rocks in the valley?"
  90,1,"I swear by this city [i.e., Makkah]"
  90,2,"And you, [O Muḥammad], are free of restriction in this city"
  90,3,"And [by] the father{1} and that which was born [of him],",footnotes:1:Said to be Adam (upon him be peace) .
